---
description: Engine classes (.c-*) must never be defined in component SCSS files — they belong in src/styles.scss only
alwaysApply: false
globs: ["src/**/*.component.scss", "src/**/*.scss", "!src/styles.scss"]
---

Never define a `.c-*` engine class (e.g. `.c-button`, `.c-card`, `.c-chip`, `.c-dropdown`) in this file.

Engine classes belong exclusively in `src/styles.scss`. Angular's view encapsulation will scope any `.c-*` class defined here, making it invisible to other components and breaking the shared engine system.

**If you need a new engine**: add it to `src/styles.scss`, then apply it in this component's template.
**If you need component-only styles**: use a descriptive local class (e.g. `.header-wrapper`) — not a `.c-*` name.
